    "The pronounced perpendicular orientation on hydrophilic surfaces promotes efficient H-bond thermal energy paths normal to the interface 113, 114.",
    "Conversely, on the CH3 surface, water molecules are 9.3% more likely to align along the surface plane (30°-135° range) than on the OH surface, reflecting the hydrophobic nature of CH3 groups.",
    "At the water/vacuum interface (film), water molecules show the least tendency to align along the normal, with a probability of lying along the plane higher than both OH and CH3 surfaces.",
    "This planar preference arises from the absence of a solid surface to anchor the molecules, allowing surface tension and dipole interactions to dominate.",
